It is noted that the contribution of each facet towards the ammonia decomposition rate was obtained independently: we first synthesized MgO cube with exclusive (100) facet; then we cleaved these cubes to expose (110) and (111) facets at various proportions (11 samples) and compared to the synthesized octahedron sample with exclusive (111) facet. Each sample was followed with the same Ru immobilization and tested for ammonia decomposition. Thus, the overall activity of each sample can be derived from the individual contributions of (100), (110), and (111) facets by resolving the equation as below.Conv.(NH3)=aX+bY+cZ\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
