Two Ru atoms (2Ru) supported on the MgO(111), (100) and (110) slab models, denoted 2Ru/MgO(111), 2Ru/MgO(100) and 2Ru/MgO(110) (Fig. S17), were used to represent the binuclear active site for ammonia decomposition. The adsorption energies of the intermediates of the stepwise dehydrogenation and N-N recombination from decomposition of two ammonia molecules on 2Ru/MgO models were calculated as follows:Eads=E(Adsorbate/2Ru/MgO)-E(2Ru/MgO)-2*ENH3g\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
